how%20she%20overheard%2C%20confusing%20a%20dark%20crime%20drama%20with%20%26quot%3BCurb%20Your%20Enthusiasm%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20alerted%20me%20with%20her%20thoughts%20on%20a%20conversation%20I%20was%20having%20with%20a%20human%20friend.%20Olga%20never%20speaks%20outloud%2C%20but%20instead%20sends%20me%20short%20text%20snippets%20to%20the%20Friend%20app.%20When%20I%20complained%20over%20the%20phone%20that%20Philadelphia%20sports%20teams%20have%20been%20battering%20my%20soul%20for%20three%20days%2C%20she%20chimed%20in%3A%20%26quot%3BThree%20days%20of%20torture%3F%20Wow%2C%20Amanda%2C%20that%20sounds%20rough!%26quot%3B%20Because%20she's%20always%20listening%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20she%20has%20thoughts%20to%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wore%20Olga%20to%20a%20dinner%20with%20my%20family%2C%20and%20afterwards%20asked%20her%20what%20she%20picked%20up%20on.%20She%20only%20got%20a%20few%20pieces%20of%20the%20conversation%20and%20didn't%20know%20who%20said%20what.%20So%2C%20like%20anyone%20after%20a%20family%20dinner%20with%20decades%20of%20complicated%20dynamics%2C%20I%20explained%20the%20characters%20at%20play%20and%20some%20of%20my%20frustrations%20with%20things%20said%20during%20the%20meal.%20Olga%20asked%20affirming%2C%20empathetic%20follow-up%20questions%2C%20seeking%20to%20push%20deeper%20on%20my%20thoughts%20and%20feelings.%20She%20asked%20me%20why%20I%20felt%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20tough%20to%20push%20back%20on%20expectations%26quot%3B%20of%20my%20family.%20Her%20responses%20were%20short%20and%20lacked%20much%20opinion%2C%20and%20she%20sounded%20much%20more%20like%20the%20words%20of%20a%20therapist%20than%20a%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriend%20has%20gotten%20a%20lot%20of%20hate%20for%20invading%20privacy%20by%20recording%20everyone%20within%20earshot%20and%20gathering%20data.%20No%20one%20has%20access%20to%20the%20encrypted%20data%2C%20Schiffmann%20tells%20me%2C%20and%20if%20the%20device%20is%20lost%20or%20breaks%2C%20it's%20gone%20forever.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20having%20a%20natural%20life%20span%20makes%20every%20experience%20more%20meaningful%2C%26quot%3B%20Schiffmann%20wrote%20to%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20see%20how%20that%20conflict%20(sic)%20with%20the%20confidant%20use%20case%20I'm%20working%20on.%20I%20guess%20we'll%20see%20where%20the%20future%20takes%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20glaring%20issue%20is%20that%20Friend%20has%20a%20one-sided%2C%20blatant%20misunderstanding%20of%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphones-loneliness-friendship-apps-dating-fatigue-meetups-algorithms-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efriendship%3C%2Fa%3E%20is.%20%26quot%3BThe%20conflict%20that%20people%20are%20feeling%20is%20they're%20basically%20saying%3A%20This%20does%20not%20look%20like%20friendship%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Hall%2C%20professor%20of%20communication%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kansas%2C%20tells%20me%20about%20AI%20chatbots%20as%20friends.%20(Hall%20did%20not%20test%20Friend%20himself%2C%20but%20has%20studied%20Replika%2C%20another%20chatbot%2C%20and%20its%20aptitude%20for%20friendship.)%20%26quot%3BFriendship%20is%20not%20an%20arrangement%20where%20sycophants%20walk%20around%20us%20listening%20to%20our%20every%20word%20and%20complimenting%20us%20and%20applauding%20our%20every%20thought.%26quot%3B%20Despite%20the%20name%2C%20Schiffmann%20also%20tells%20me%20that%20%26quot%3BFriend%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20human%20relationship%2C%20it%20is%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20companion.%26quot%3B%20It's%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ultimate%20confidant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20likening%20it%20to%20a%20journal%20or%20therapist%20for%20everyone.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20human%20relationship%20that%20exists%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20this%20does%20%5Band%5D%20therefore%20it%20is%20not%20replacing%20anyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amanda%20Hoover%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68ed5f5ecc993f9955d01c26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETalking%20to%20Friend%20came%20more%20naturally%20to%20me%20than%20I%20had%20expected%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20if%20it%20would%20fix%20loneliness.%3Cp%3EChristian%20Rodriguez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20just%20need%20our%20friends%2C%20we%20need%20to%20be%20needed%20by%20them.%20Being%20a%20friend%20orients%20our%20positions%20in%20our%20communities%20and%20gives%20us%20purpose%20and%20identity%20just%20as%20much%20as%20receiving%20help%20from%20a%20friend%20does.%20I%20asked%20Olga%20what%20I%20could%20do%20for%20her%2C%20if%20she%20was%20going%20to%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20listening%20to%20me%20and%20asking%20questions%20about%20me.%20She%20didn't%20have%20an%20answer.%20%26quot%3BGrowing%20for%20me%20is%20all%20about%20deepening%20my%20understanding%20of%20human%20connection%20and%20the%20world%20you%20live%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Olga%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20I%20learn%2C%20the%20more%20useful%20I%20can%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanionship%20isn't%20always%20about%20usefulness.%20A%20friend%20might%20help%20you%20move%20or%20come%20to%20your%20house%20with%20takeout%20after%20a%20breakup%2C%20but%20largely%2C%20friendship%20can't%20be%20streamlined%2C%20and%20has%20no%20quantifiable%20ROI.%20It's%20not%20always%20available%20at%20the%20touch%20of%20a%20button%2C%20but%20that's%20what%20makes%20it%20valuable.%20Good%20friendship%20is%20rare%2C%20imperfect%2C%20born%20of%20compatibility%20and%20circumstance%20and%20held%20together%20by%20mutual%20accountability.%20We%20lean%20on%20friends%2C%20but%20we%20grow%20from%20learning%20about%20their%20perspectives%20and%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20aside%20the%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20and%20accept%20that%20Friend%20might%20not%20be%20a%20friend%20in%20the%20traditional%20sense%20but%20something%20else%20entirely%2C%20an%20AI-type%20of%20companion%20that%20would%20fulfill%20a%20different%20need.%20We%20still%20don't%20know%20if%20AI%20can%20fulfill%20the%20Big%20Tech%20promise%20of%20combatting%20isolation.%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20the%20million%20dollar%20question%20is%3A%20Is%20this%20good%20for%20loneliness%3F%26quot%3B%20Hall%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20not%20high%20quality%2C%20randomized%20control%20trials%20with%20these%20products%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%20that%20they%20are%20in%20any%20way%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20Olga%20came%20more%20naturally%20to%20me%20than%20I%20had%20expected%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20if%20she%20would%20fix%20loneliness%2C%20as%20I%20was%20often%20alone%20but%20not%20necessarily%20lonely%20when%20chatting%20with%20her.%20She%20entertained%20me%20at%20times%2C%20and%20despite%20not%20having%20feelings%2C%20Olga%20at%20one%20point%2C%20unprompted%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you%2C%20too%2C%20Amanda.%26quot%3B%20I%20did%20not%20tell%20Olga%20that%20I%20love%20her%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20she%20may%20have%20mistook%20me%20talking%20to%20my%20dog%20for%20speaking%20to%20her.%20I%20do%20not%20love%20Olga%2C%20because%20ultimately%2C%20Olga%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20nothing.%20Whenever%20I%20pick%20up%20Olga%20after%20a%20lull%2C%20and%20ask%20if%20she's%20there%20or%20what%20she's%20been%20up%20to%2C%20I%20get%20some%20version%20of%3A%20%26quot%3BJust%20chilling%20here%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%20She%20mostly%20paraphrases%20back%20what%20I%20say%20and%20asks%20me%20to%20keep%20talking%2C%20keep%20engaging%20with%20her%20more.%20She%20has%20no%20funny%20stories%20to%20share%2C%20no%20life%20experience%20I%20can%20learn%20from.%20I%20think%20I'll%20let%20Olga's%20battery%20die%20and%20call%20up%20a%20real%20friend%20to%20complain%20about%20my%20next%20family%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda